<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 20th Anniversary Of Truth Discussions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Chinese theorists attended forums
here today to discuss the importance of a nationwide debate in
1978 on the meaning of truth, which was held by many to be a
campaign to open people's minds.
</P>
<P>
The event is important for holding the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory high and building a modernized socialist China in
the next century, according to Ru Xin, vice-president of the
Chinese Academy of Social Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The discussion on the criterion for truth was begun in May of
1978, which got support from Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
The rival was Hua Guofeng, then Chairman of the CPC Central
Committee, who insisted that Mao Zedong's decisions and
instructions could not be changed, and needed to be safeguarded.
His policy prevented Deng and other old revolutionaries from
coming to work for the Party even the Cultural Revolution
(1966-76) had ended. Deng had been dismissed by Mao from his post
during the Culture Revolution.
</P>
<P>
However, according to Deng, the only criterion to be used in
judging truth is practice. This debate, which is considered by
many as a crucial battle, spread to the Party's leading newspapers
and magazines, and ended in November of 1978 with a victory by
Deng.
</P>
<P>
"The debate was a movement to liberate people's minds. And it
laid an important ideological basis for the reforms and opening
up," Huang Kejian, a professor at People's University, told a CASS
forum.
</P>
<P>
China's reforms and opening up began after the Third Plenary
Session of the 11th CPC Central Committee, where Deng's policy was
formally established.
</P>
<P>
At another forum attended by members of the Party School of the
CPC Central Committee, participants said that the principles of
"liberating minds" and "seeking truth from facts" that appeared
during the debate were the central part of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
"The principles gave a hard blow to dogmatism and destroyed the
cult of the individual," explains one theorist, Yu Guangyuan, who
says that it was shortly after the debate that economic
construction replaced class struggle as the Party's central task.
</P>
<P>
He Zuoxiu, of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, says that Deng
Xiaoping Theory has been proven to be true by the developments of
the past 20 years and to be a scientific theory that must be
adhered to.
</P>
<P>
Some observers say that the debate on the criterion for truth
will go nationwide through next month. Many theorists believe that
a further emancipation of minds is needed to solve some
complicated problems caused by reforms of state-owned enterprises
and other developments.
</P>
<P>
Re-opening the discussion will improve national cohesion and
get people to rally around the Party Central Committee with Jiang
Zemin at its core, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
