<HEADLINE> UNDP Supports Poverty Eradication in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) has launched a 1.5 million U.S. dollar
project in China's Guangxi Province to help 4,500 poor households
living in extreme poverty, it was announced here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The effort aims at improving income-levels and conditions for
some 22,500 people who live in poor farming counties where per
capita income is less than 50 dollars a year, UNDP said in a press
release.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural equipment, training and support services will be
provided to upgrade farming productivity and income generating
activities, it said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
