<HEADLINE> Japan Supports UNDP Program in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Japan has approved a 4.2
million U.S. dollar contribution to the United Nations Development
Program (UNDP) Trust Fund for reconstruction of Rwanda, according
to UNDP.
</P>
<P>
Major part of the money will be spent on strengthening the
Kigali Institute for Science and Technology with an aim to help
the country meet its urgent need for skilled personnel in
technical field, UNDP said in a press release on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Cooperation Agency has also joined UNDP in the
program, UNDP added.  
</P>
