<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Council Halts Pyramid Sales Schemes In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Pyramid sales schemes have been
outlawed as of today in China, the State Council said in a
circular today, pointing out that they were not suited to national
conditions and have done some serious harm.
</P>
<P>
It announced that China's marketing system is far from
developed and that its management methods are backward, and that
through various pyramid schemes a number of unscrupulous people
have engaged in a series of illegal activities in recent years,
behaving badly, getting involved in underworld gangs, and preying
on superstitions.
</P>
<P>
Any businesses that registered for pyramid sales before the
State Council announcement have to halt the practice before
October 31. And they should register another form of business to
replace the pyramid sales and cancel the original registration.
</P>
<P>
Industrial and commercial departments will immediately halt all
illegal pyramid sales and penalize any persons who are involved in
unauthorized pyramid sales with fines or more severe penalties in
accordance with the Chinese Criminal Code.
</P>
<P>
The ban calls for government departments to enforce the law on
all forms of pyramid sales better.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
