<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Elected Bank for Int'l Settlement 1st Overseas Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Bank for International
Settlement (BIS) plans to establish in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) a Representative Office to serve as
its regional office for Asia and the Pacific, it was announced
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Being the first overseas office for the BIS to strengthen its
cooperation with central banks and monetary authorities in the
region, the office is expected to commence operation in July this
year.
</P>
<P>
The BIS, established in 1930, is a prestigious international
organization of central banks and monetary authorities in Basle,
Switzerland. Known as the "bank of central banks", it provides
banking and investment services to central banking institutions.
</P>
<P>
It is also a forum for international monetary cooperation,
providing a meeting place for central banks to discuss issues of
mutual concern and set international standards for the promotion
of international financial stability.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong SAR's Financial Secretary Donald Tsang said, "we
fully support the activities of the BIS and welcome their plan to
set up its first overseas office in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"As a leading international financial center, Hong Kong is well
placed to be the seat of the Representative Office in Asia. Hong
Kong stands to benefit from being the focal point of BIS
activities in the region," he added.
</P>
<P>
Tsang described the establishment of the Office in Hong Kong as
"an important milestone in the development of Hong Kong's
relationship with the BIS."
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) became a member of the
BIS in November 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
