<HEADLINE> Botswana Inflation Drops in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Botswana's year-on-year
inflation dropped to 6.9 percent in March from the 7.0 percent in
February, South African Press Association reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It has been on a downward trend for two years. In March 1996,
it stood at 10.2 percent and in March 1997, it was 9.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The all items consumer price index rose 0.8 percent in March
over February to 110.3 points on a base of 100 in November 1996.
</P>
<P>
The cost of living in Botswana has risen 16.8 percent since
March 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
