<HEADLINE> UNDP Supports Computer Refurbishing Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) has donated hundreds of old and
unusable computers to a unique program to save the equipment
instead of sending it to a landfill.
</P>
<P>
The New-York based LINCT Coalition receives and upgrades the
PCs while disposing of toxic and unusable parts. The refurbished
PCs are then distributed to non-profit organizations locally and
internationally, UNDP said in a press release here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
UNDP's donation is part of an effort to expand sound
environmental practices within the organization.
</P>
<P>
Other "greening" efforts include the establishment of a
comprehensive recycling program and environmentally-sound
procurement specifications, UNDP said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
