<HEADLINE> Candidates Nominated for Lesotho's General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 400 candidates
have been nominated by 12 political parties and 30 independents
for Lesotho's May 23 general election, South African Press
Association reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The country's Independent Electoral Commission Tuesday
released the list of candidates, 32 days before the mountain
kingdom's polls.
</P>
<P>
Parties with the highest number of candidates include the
ruling Lesotho Congress for Democracy and the Basotho National
Party, each with 79. The Basutoland Congress Party has 78 and
Marematlou Freedom Party 56. 
</P>
