<HEADLINE> Uganda Steps up Measures Against Blasts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan president Yoweri
Museveni said Tuesday afternoon that his country has taken
effective measures to prevent blasts.
</P>
<P>
The president made these remarks at a press conference after
his four-day state visit to Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
He said the terrorists have been identified and some arrests
were made in connection with the recent bomb explosions in the
capital city which killed five people and injured some others.
</P>
<P>
The terrorism, he added, was linked with a third country and
Uganda has restricted travels to and from that country. He also
said measures had been taken to enhance people's awareness of
security.
</P>
<P>
There were three blasts this month and a new national task
force has been formed to cope with the growing terrorist
activities in the east African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
