<HEADLINE> Nearly 8,000 Somali Refugees Repatriated from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Close to 8,000 Somali
refugees who took shelter at the Dermenajo refugee camp in east
Ethiopia were repatriated to their homeland last week, the
Ethiopian News Agency reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Tsegaye Meheretu, head of Refugees
Coordinating Office in Ethiopia's Somali Region, as saying that
the office has transported the refugees to Hargessa and Borema
areas in northern Somalia in collaboration with the United
Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
The official said some 19,867 Somali refugees in Teferi-Ber,
Hartishek and Dermenajo refugee camps have been taken to the
place of their origin in a series of repatriation operations
since last year.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed a plan to repatriate 60,000 more voluntary
Somali refugees in the near future. 
</P>
