<HEADLINE> Borys Tarasyuk Appointed Ukraine Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Borys Tarasyuk has been
appointed Ukraine's new foreign minister, the Permanent Mission of
Ukraine to the United Nations announced here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He replaced Hennadiy Udovenko as the latter was elected member
of the nation's parliament and resigned from the post of minister
in accordance with the country's constitution, the Mission said in
a press release.
</P>
<P>
Borys Tarasyuk, 49, is a career diplomat and has served as
Ukraine's' ambassador to Belgium, the Netherlands and Luxembourg.
He was Ukraine's First Deputy Foreign Minister in 1994-1995.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko will work in the Ukrainian Parliament and continue his
Presidency at the United Nations General Assembly until his
one-year term in that capacity ends, the Mission said.
</P>
<P>
In his parting statement, the Mission added, Udovenko wished
Ukraine's Foreign Ministry "not to stop spinning its wheels on the
way to Ukraine's intergration into European and Trans-Atlantic
structures", while underlining the necessity to enhance efforts
aimed at deepening its cooperation with Russia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
