<HEADLINE> UNICEF, WWF to Work Jointly on Freshwater </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Children's Fund (UNICEF) and the World Wide Fund for Nature (WWF)
will work together to seek solutions to the emerging global
freshwater crisis.
</P>
<P>
This was expressed by a Memorandum of Understanding signed
between the two organizations here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two U.N. bodies will undertake joint projects at the local,
national and regional levels to promote sustainable community
management of water resources.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony took place as the world's governments are
negotiating an action plan on freshwater resources under the U.N.
Commission on Sustainable Development at its annual session from
April 20-may 1 here.
</P>
<P>
Over 2 million children under the age of five die each year as
a result of unsafe water and poor environmental sanitation,
according to UNICEF Program Division Director Sadig Rasheed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
