<HEADLINE> Chairmen of Parliament Want Meeting with Yeltsin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Chairmen of the lower and
upper houses of Russia's parliament on Tuesday expressed hope to
meet with Russian President Boris Yeltsin before the third Duma
vote on premier's nomination scheduled for April 24, the Interfax
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
State Duma Chairman Gennady Seleznyov said after his meeting
with Federation Council Chairman Yegor Stroyev that "We want the
president to lift the veil in the run-up to the third ballot on
Premier candidacy Sergei Kiriyenko in the Duma, (and to reveal)
which members of the previous government will include."
</P>
<P>
