deem it necessary for him to deliver a report. They took a more
radical position and invited Kiriyenko to their meeting tomorrow
so that he will answer all unclear questions, the Duma speaker
said.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of leftist and center-left parties and movements in the
Duma Tuesday decided to prevent dissolution of the parliament's
lower chamber by approval of Kiriyenko's candidacy on Friday,
Seleznyov declared.
</P>
<P>
He said that he will tell the Communist Party of Russia's
Central Committee on Thursday that the leftist deputies do not
want the Duma to be dissolved. 
</P>
