<HEADLINE> Iran Finds New Gas Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tehran, April 21(Xinhua) -- Iran announced on Tuesday that it
has found a new gas field with 2.1 trillion cubic feet of gas and
10.5 million barrels of liquid gas in southern part of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official news agency IRNA quoted Deputy Oil
Minister Ali Hashemi as saying that the gas field was found in
Gordan, 135 kilometers from Shiraz, the capital city of Fars
province.
</P>
<P>
Hashemi said the new gas reserve is worth three billion
U.S. dollars and its liquid gas is worth 200 million dollars,
adding that the Oil Ministry has planned to develop the gas field
within the next two years.
</P>
<P>
After Russia, Iran ranks the second in the world with a proven
gas reserve of 21 trillion cubic meters. 
