<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- About 7,000 citizens in central
Angola's Huila Province fled their home as a large number of
remnants of the former rebel UNITA gathered at Cutenda Town for
fresh attacks.
</P>
<P>
Government officials at the Cutenda Town was quoted by the
Angolan News Agency as saying Tuesday that a few days ago UNITA
leaders at the town had evacuated from the place with some
villagers, which kindled horror and many in the town and the
adjacent Chicomba Town fled their home.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that about 20 people came to the refugee center
in Matala City near Cutenda and Chicomba Towns each day for fear
of maltreatment by the building-up UNITA forces.
</P>
<P>
In anther incident, a vehicle in Negola Town in Huila Province
was attacked by the UNITA gunmen Sunday, injuring eight, with 50
still missing.
</P>
<P>
This is the fifth vehicle attacked by UNITA forces in the past
few weeks, in which six people were killed and over 30 injured.
</P>
<P>
The central Angola's Huila, Benguela and Blondin Beye
provinces, has been regarded as "dangerous triangular" by Blondin
Beye, the UN special envoy to Angola.
</P>
<P>
UN Secretary General Koffi Annan has talked about the issue in
his report to the Security Council, calling for actions to
restore stability in the region.  
</P>
