<HEADLINE> Saudi King Fahd Meets Arafat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 21 (Xinhua) -- President of the Palestinian
National Authority Yasser Arafat met King Fahd Bin Abdel Aziz of
Saudi Arabia in Saudi Red Sea port city of Jeddah Tuesday to
discuss the stalled Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Arafat reiterated the Palestinian call to hold an emergency
Arab summit to announce an united Arab position on the
deteriorating situation in the peace process and urge the Israeli
right-wing government to implement the signed agreements with the
Palestinians, according to Saudi Press Agency reports reaching
here.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who arrived in Saudi Arabia earlier Tuesday, also met
with Saudi Crown Prince and deputy Prime Minister Abdullah Bin
Abdel Aziz.
</P>
<P>
During his talks with the Saudi leaders, Arafat also
discussed bilateral relations and developments in the Arab,
Islamic and international arenas, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat and King Fahd also assessed the results of British
Prime Minister Tony Blair's recent tour to the region aimed at
pushing forward the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Blair proposed hosting a summit between Arafat and Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in London next month to salvage
the peace process. Arafat and Netanyahu have accepted the proposal.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian-Israeli talks have been stalled since March 1997
when Israel began construction of a new Jewish settlement in
East Jerusalem. 
</P>
