<HEADLINE> Demirel: Peace to Accelerate Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel said Tuesday that regional peace will accelerate the
economic development in the balkans.
</P>
<P>
Demirel made the remarks while meeting Macedonian Foreign
Minister Blagoj Handziski, who arrived here Monday for a two-day
official visit.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish president expressed his hope that Macedonia would
use its influence on the Belgrade administration to help realize
peace in Yugoslavia's troubled region of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem told reporters
that "Macedonia's membership to NATO is essential. In order to
achieve stability in the Balkans, Macedonia's NATO membership
should be a primary objective. Turkey wholeheartedly supports
Macedonia's bid and is ready to do its utmost on this issue."
</P>
<P>
Cem also emphasized the significance of Turkey's cooperation
with Macedonia given the complications of the present situation
in the Balkans, saying that ways of improving economic
cooperation with Macedonia would be carefully considered.
</P>
<P>
Handziski, for his part, praised Turkey's efforts for enhancing
stability in southeastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on bilateral relations, the Macedonian foreign
minister expressed satisfaction with the current ties, saying
that Macedonia has signed a number of agreements with Turkey.
</P>
</TEXT>
