<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Tries to Control Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Environmental Council of
Zambia (ECZ) has created a department on clearner industrial
production to control pollution, ECZ Chief Inspector Paul Banda
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Paul Banda said that ECZ supports voluntary environmtal
programs aimed at improving efficiency and profitability in the
industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening meeting of the first ever
Norwegian-Zambian cleaner production training workshop held in
Kabwe in central Zambia, Paul Banda said, "The objectives of the
workshop are in line with the overall mandate of the ECZ to
provide for a clean and healthy environment for all-human beings,
animals and plants."
</P>
<P>
He urged industries to reduce waste generation and pollution
and start to use energy and raw materials more efficiently, thus
maximizing profits.
</P>
<P>
Banda cited as "realf life" examples from African industries
in Egypt and Tanzania where applied clearner production
principles improve environmental conditions and reduce health
hazards.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive of the Zambia Association of Chambers of
Commerce and Industry (ZACCI), Gideon Phiri warned that Zambia
will be a victime of industrial success of developed countries if
industries do not apply the concept of clearner production.
</P>
<P>
But he said that many industries in the country are "waking up
and realizing" the importance of preventing industrial pollution.
</P>
<P>
Thirty participants from various industries are attending the
four-day workshop. 
</P>
</TEXT>
