<HEADLINE> Warring Afghan Factions to Hold Meeting in Islamabad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Representatives of the Afghan
Taliban militia and the opposition Northern Alliance are expected
to hold a meeting of the joint Steering Committee on Afghanistan
here on April 25.
</P>
<P>
The face-to-face meeting will discuss immediate issues of
maintaining ceasefire and preparing the ground for the holding of
a meeting of the Ulema (Scholar) Commission, a report by the
Associated Press of Pakistan Wednesday quoted Afghan sources as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the meeting is also likely to discuss other issues
including release of prisoners, removal of blockade of central
Afghanistan and establishment of a broad-based government, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will take place here under the auspices of the
United Nations and the Organization of Islamic Conference. The
Pakistani government will extend necessary hospitality to
facilitate the meeting, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The agreement between the Taliban and the Northern Alliance to
hold the meeting was reached in the talks held here Tuesday, which
 were attended by representatives of the Taliban, the Northern
Alliance, the United Nations and the government of Pakistan,
according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
