<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Comments On Finding Jobs For Unemployed Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji told a State
Council meeting in Beijing today that the Chinese Communist Party
and the Government are confident they can solve the employment
problem for urban people and are sure of establishing a social
security system with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The loss of jobs is inevitable in the course of readjusting the
industrial structure and building a socialist market economy, Zhu
said, and as the economic structure and science and technology
improve, the number of the laid-off will increase, so
re-employment is a normal and long-term process.
</P>
<P>
He said that a rudimentary plan to offer basic needs and new
jobs to workers who are laid off has been formed and he hoped that
departments will get opinions from various sectors.
</P>
<P>
Some members of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference who were present at the meeting
expressed great concern about the re-employment question and said
they are satisfied with the arrangements of the CPC Central
Committee and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
They said that government departments need to help workers
change their concept of employment and try to find jobs in other
fields like the service trade and non-state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Also present at today's forum were Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo,
State Councillor and Secretary General of the State Council Wang
Zhongyu, and a number of vice-chairmen of the CPPCC National
Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
