<HEADLINE> HK's 1st Central Slaughter Facility for Live Ducks to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's first ever central
slaughter facility for live ducks and other water birds will start
operation early Thursday morning in a poultry stall at the Western
Wholesale Food Market.
</P>
<P>
The stall has obtained a Fresh Provision Shop license from the
Urban Services Department (USD) here on Wednesday. It was the
first such license ever issued for the purpose.
</P>
<P>
It begins operation early Thursday morning and is expected to
provide a few hundred freshly slaughtered, locally-bred ducks on
the first morning, a spokesman for the Agriculture and Fisheries
Department (AFD) announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The samples of water birds from these local farms had been
tested by AFD staff to be free from H5N1 virus.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) government
had designed the poultry market as centralized facility for the
slaughtering and dressing of water birds under the new policy
requiring the segregation of live chickens and water birds
announced in February.
</P>
<P>
The original facilities of the stalls in the market had to be
updated to meet the necessary requirements for obtaining a Fresh
Provision Shop license. 
</P>
</TEXT>
