<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Technology Adds Value to HK Economy: Businessman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- New technology plays a critical
role in building Hong Kong into Asia's leading metropolitan
economy, a well-known Hong Kong businessman said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a seminar on Hong Kong's competitiveness, Chairman
of the Hong Kong Trade Development Council Victor Fung described
Hong Kong as a "metropolitan economy," like London and New York,
which is externally oriented and services dominated.
</P>
<P>
No other regional city is as well-positioned as Hong Kong to
assume the role of the leading metropolitan economy in the Asia
Pacific region, Fung stressed.
</P>
<P>
But it doesn't mean bringing every type of economic activity
inside Hong Kong. "We should focus Hong Kong's role as a
management center, a financial center, and a center for the
headquarters of multinational firms doing business in the region,
among others," he continued.
</P>
<P>
But in achieving the leading position in the region Hong Kong
faces two inter-linked challenges: upgrading the technological
capacities of Hong Kong firms and upgrading the skills of the
workforce, the businessman noted.
</P>
<P>
"This means that inside Hong Kong's borders we must build a
first-class technological environment for our companies," Fung
said, adding that the hardest task will be to equip Hong Kong's
workforce with the sophisticated skills necessary to create and
extract the greatest value from the new technologies.
</P>
<P>
In terms of Hong Kong's technological environment and the
technological sophistication of the workforce, Hong Kong stands
just in the middle of the pack over the world. "We need to aim
for the very top," Fung noted.
</P>
<P>
A large number of government officials, business people and
economic experts attended the half-day seminar organized by the
government's Central Policy Unit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
