"The president will hold a meeting with the State Duma speaker,
Gennady Seleznyov, and Federation Council Chairman Yegor Stroyev
on Thursday," a Kremlin spokesman said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Gennady Zyuganov, leader of the Russian Communist
Party, the largest Duma faction, said the Communists' stand on
this issue remains unchanged and they will reject Kiriyenko Friday.
</P>
<P>
