<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets Leaders of Japanese Parties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 22 (Xinhua)-- China's new Vice-President Hu Jintao
said Wednesday that party diplomacy has played an important role
in promoting bilateral relations and mutual understanding between
China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
During separate meetings with leaders of the Japanese parties,
Hu called for joint efforts by Chinese and Japanese political
parties to boost the two countries' friendly ties as they went
into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Communist Party is ready to strengthen its
exchanges and cooperation with the political parties in Japan on
the basis of independence, equality, mutual respect and
non-interference in each other's internal affairs, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
Among the party leaders Hu met are Koichi Kato of Japan's
ruling Liberal Democratic Party, Takako Doi of the Social
Democratic Party (SDP), Hiroyuki Sonoda of New Party Sakigake and
Ichiro Ozawa of Liberal Party.
</P>
<P>
Hu said the statesmen of China and Japan shoulder the
responsibility of advancing a long-term, stable and
good-neighborly bilateral relationship oriented towards the next
century.
</P>
<P>
To this end, it's very important to strictly abide by the
spirit and principles set in the Sino-Japanese Joint Statement and
the Peace and Friendship Treaty, take lessons from history, expand
mutually beneficial cooperation and handle bilateral ties in a
responsible manner, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that the two countries should educate their young
generations with the spirit of long-term Sino-Japanese friendship,
and encourage them to contribute to bilateral, friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
The leaders of the Japanese political parties told Hu that they
are willing to reinforce exchanges and cooperation with the
Communist Party of China (CPC), and work for the comprehensive
development of Japan-China good-neighborly ties.
</P>
<P>
Koichi Kato, secretary-general of Japan's ruling Liberal
Democratic Party (LDP), said that both Japan and China are big
nations and the LDP is ready to make in-depth exchanges of views
with the CPC to contribute to understanding and friendship between
the peoples of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Takako Doi, head of the Social Democratic Party (SDP), said
regular consultations between her party and the CPC, which started
in 1983, have been playing an important role in enhancing
friendship between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
The SDP, by abiding by the principles of Japan-China Joint
Statement and the Japan-China Peace and Friendship Treaty, and by
not forgetting the history, will continue its efforts towards
forging "new era-oriented" Sino-Japanese ties, Doi said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice-president, who arrived here Tuesday for a
six-day visit, also met leaders from New Democratic Party of
Japan, New Peace Party and Komei Party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
