<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Portuguese PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, Chairman of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress, in a meeting with
Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio Guterres here today, said that
bilateral co-operation in various sectors has continued to develop
since the two countries established diplomatic ties in 1979.
</P>
<P>
These contacts have deepened mutual understanding and
friendship between the two people and stimulated bilateral
relations, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Guterres noted that China plays an important role in
maintaining world stability, and its efforts in offsetting the
effects of the Asian financial crisis are a sign of its maturity
and spirit of responsibility.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that, as preparation for Macao's handover enters
the last stage, the two countries should cooperate more on the
smooth handover in accordance with the joint statement.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's smooth handover and its continued prosperity and
stability have attracted world attention, Li pointed out, and said
he believes that efforts by China and Portugal will see to it that
the issue of Macao is well handled.
</P>
<P>
Guterres said that Portugal will make its own effort for this
and he believed that the Portugal-China ties will be closer after
the handover of Macao.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders said they believe that Sino-Portuguese
relations will be further developed after 1999. They also
discussed bilateral economic cooperation, the Asian financial
crisis, and the European Union. 
</P>
