<HEADLINE> 8 People Killed by Cholera in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- At least 119 people have been
stricken and eight of them killed by cholera in the southern
Philippines, the Philippine News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report said there were 104 cases of suspected cholera in
five villages in the remote town of Upi, Magunidanao province,
where all the deaths were confirmed.
</P>
<P>
Provincial health officer Tahir Sulaik was quoted as saying
that of the fatalities, two were adults and the rest were children
under five years old.
</P>
<P>
In two other places neighboring the province, 15 children were
also being treated for cholera symptoms, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The southern Philippines has been hit by drought brought about
by El Nino during the past two months. At least 64 people have
reportedly died in famine caused by the drought. 
</P>
</TEXT>
