General Staff of the People's Liberation Army(PLA), in a meeting
here today with Croatian Lieutenant General Pavao Miljavac, said
that the Croatian military leader's visit to China has opened a
new chapter in the history of the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that, since the establishment of diplomatic relations,
China and Croatia have seen good development in cooperative ties
in politics, the economy, culture and science and technology, and
that the Chinese government and PLA place great importance on
friendly and cooperative relations with Croatia.
</P>
<P>
Miljavac's visit is the first by a high-ranking officer of the
Croatian armed forces and benefits friendly relations between the
two armed forces and cooperative ties between the two countries,
Fu noted.
</P>
<P>
Fu said he believes that with joint efforts by both sides,
relations between the two armed forces will grow on the basis of
mutual respect and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Miljavac is chief of general staff of the Croatian armed
forces. He said that relations between Croatia and China have a
good foundation and many common points can be found in their
military forces and he said he hope that the friendly relations
will be strengthened. 
</P>
