<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tung Encourages HK's Future Immigration Officers to Serve the SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa said
here Wednesday that the Immigration Department plays an important
role in maintaining the social stability and internal security of
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a passing out parade of the Immigration Service
Training School, Tung told the young people participating the
parade that they will add new strength to the Immigration
Department and they have chosen a meaningful career for the
well-being of the society.
</P>
<P>
While exercising effective immigration control at Hong Kong's
land, sea and air entry points, the department works closely with
the Police and the Labor Department in detecting illegal
immigration and illegal employment, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Department has also made remarkable
achievements in the investigation of and the combat against the
use of forged documents, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, apart from handling a huge amount of day-to-day work,
the department was heavily involved in the work connected with the
 return of Hong Kong to the motherland, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
This work includes the issue of the HKSAR passports; the
implementation of the provisions of the Basic Law on the right of
abode; the implementation of new arrangements for overseas issue
of travel documents, visas and permits for entry into Hong Kong;
and the handling of all matters relating to nationality on behalf
of the Central People's Government.
</P>
<P>
In the face of these historical missions, all members of the
Immigration Service could pride themselves on the dedication and
professionalism they displayed in the successful completion of all
 the important tasks they were charged with, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the continued efforts in promoting the HKSAR
passport to the governments of foreign countries and securing the
grant of visa-free access to foreign countries for HKSAR passport
holders, the department is actively examining ways to facilitate
the entry of visitors, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Department has also striven for further improvement in the
efficiency and quality of services through policy and procedural
reviews, and the use of advanced technology, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the department has completed the restructuring of
the immigration officer grade and resumed the recruitment of
immigration officers, Tung said.
</P>
<P>
"After intensive and tough induction training, you would
definitely help the Department in serving the community," Tung
told the trainees. "I hope that you all take pride in the service
you are going to render," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
