<HEADLINE> Laos, U.S. Seek Missing American Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Laos and the United States are
joining forces to account for Americans missing in action in the
inland Southeast Asian nation during the Indochina war.
</P>
<P>
Joint technical teams have undertaken fresh operations to seek
those missing of the war which broke out in 1960s, Lao Foreign
Ministry said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The move is the third one under a 1997-1998 joint operation
plan.
</P>
<P>
The teams have made one excavation in Laos' central Khammouane
province, three in central Savannakhet province, and another in
southern Sekong province.
</P>
<P>
Among the findings are debris of aircraft, bones and teeth, as
well as some identification cards of pilots, which will be sent to
the U.S. for further analysis and identification.
</P>
<P>
The move is being carried out in response to the requests of
Washington as well as families of Americans still missing in
action. 
</P>
</TEXT>
