<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Portuguese Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting here today with Portugal's Prime Minister Antonio
Guterres, said that China and Portugal and the European Union
should make joint efforts to bring peace, stability and prosperity
to the world in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the prime minister's visit is very important
because of Macao's return to China next year, and that friendly
relations between China and Portugal will be further promoted and
cooperation in the last phase of the transition period
strengthened through this visit.
</P>
<P>
He said that as long as both parties emphasize the overall
situation and long-term stability and development of Macao, and
solve certain problems, the transition will be smooth.
</P>
<P>
China values its relations with Portugal, Jiang said, and is
willing to further develop long-term friendly and cooperative
relations based on mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit. He
said he is satisfied with the bilateral relations that have
developed since diplomatic ties were established 19 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Guterres said that political relations between the two
countries are good, and economic cooperation is fruitful.
</P>
