<HEADLINE> Macao Promotion Week Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A promotion campaign to introduce
Macao to more people in China's inland cities will be carried out
from May, organizers said here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The "Macao Publicity Week" will be conducted in Beijing,
Shanghai, Shenyang, Chongqing, Guangzhou and Macao, said Qi
Tiexie, a spokesman of the Organizing Committee of the Macao
Publicity Week in a press conference.
</P>
<P>
The publicity week consists of a wide-ranging events -- photo
exhibitions on Macao's current situation and history, on the
signing of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Declaration and on Macao's
industry and trade, Macao stamp exhibition, lectures of Macao
Basic Law, Macao calligraphic and painting works exhibition, and
small exposition of Macao's tourism, real estate, fashion, food
and books.
</P>
<P>
"The aim of the publicity week is to promote the basic law of
Macao and let more people know Macao's historical changes, current
situation and customs on the eve of Macao handover," Qi said.
</P>
<P>
The first leg of the campaign will start in mid-May in
Beijing, and the last leg is expected to begin in Macao around
December 20 this year, the one year countdown anniversary of
Macao's handover.
</P>
<P>
The campaign is sponsored by the Macao Chinese Enterprises
Association, the Macao Daily News and an import and export company
under the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation.  
