<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets With Japanese Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao said Wednesday that the development of Sino-Japanese
friendly and cooperative ties has brought great benefits to the
two countries and the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Hu made the remarks here during a meeting with Japanese Foreign
Minister Keizo Obuchi.
</P>
<P>
Noting that bilateral relations have made remarkable progress
in various fields since the normalization of diplomatic ties
between the two countries, Hu expressed appreciation over Japan's
positive attitude in promoting bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Hu also said it was his belief that the significant visit to
Japan by Chinese President Jiang Zemin this fall, to mark the 20th
anniversary of the signing of the China-Japan Peace and Friendship
Treaty, will further boost the development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
China and Japan are two influential countries in Asia and the
world, Hu said. In the nearing 21st century, the enhancement of
good neighborly ties on the basis of adhering to the Sino-Japanese
Joint Statement and the Sino-Japanese Peace and Friendship Treaty
not only conforms to the fundmental interests of the two peoples,
but is conducive to peace, stability and prosperity in Asia and
the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Hu hoped Japan would face up to history, walk along the road of
peaceful development, correctly handle issues relating to its
relations with Taiwan, and never do anything harmful to China's
cause of reunification.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese Communist Party and the government would
consistently uphold a friendly policy towards Japan, and were
willing to make joint efforts with Japan to promote long-term,
stable and healthy development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Referring to bilateral economic ties, Hu said such relations
constitute important parts of bilateral friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
Pointing out that China and Japan are complementary in
resources, technology and markets, Hu said he hoped the two
countries would further promote economic trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Congratulating Hu on his assuming the Chinese vice-presidency,
Obuchi said he agreed with Hu's evaluation of Sino-Japanese
relations.
</P>
<P>
Japan will work for friendly Sino-Japanese ties oriented toward
the next century on the basis of serious introspection over the
past unfortunate history, Obuchi said.
</P>
<P>
Talking about Hu's current trip and the forthcoming visit to
Japan by Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Obuchi said it was rare
for China's president and vice president to visit Japan within one
year. He believed the visits would greatly boost bilateral
friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
Following the meeting, Obuchi hosted a banquet in honor of Hu.
</P>
</TEXT>
