<HEADLINE> 50,000 Military Officers To Be Transferred To Civilian Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua)-- About 50,000 officers from the
People's Liberation Army and the armed police force will be
transferred to civilian work this year.
</P>
<P>
A national meeting on the placement of these officers that
concluded here today called concerned departments to do a good job
in making appropriate arrangements for the placement of these
people.
</P>
<P>
The meeting pointed out that to help these people find civilian
jobs that suit them best in terms of intelligence and competence
has a direct bearing on the success of China's disarmament plan.
</P>
<P>
At the 15th national congress of the Chinese Communist Party
last October, the Party's general secretary jiang Zemin announced
that beginning 1998, China would reduce its armed forces by
500,000 by year 2,000.
</P>
<P>
The meeting said any Party and government organizations and
enterprises should not refuse to accept the demobilized officers
under any excuses while the demobilized armymen should take the
interest of the whole into account and be cooperative in this
regard. 
</P>
