<HEADLINE> Indian Govt to Speed up Insurance Sector Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Indian Minister of State for
Finance R. K. Kumar said Wednesday that insurance sector reform in
the country must proceed quickly to enable strengthening of the
Indian financial sector.
</P>
<P>
It would also provide vital long term savings for investments
in the infrastructure sector, he said while addressing an
international conference on insurance here.
</P>
<P>
Multinationals and developed countries have time and again
urged India to open up its insurance sector to the outside world,
yet the previous governments were quite cautious on the issue.
</P>
<P>
Monopoly in any sector is not conducive to efficiency and it is
necessary to provide competition to the state owned insurance
companies like life insurance corporation and general insurance
corporation by private sector Indian companies, he said.
</P>
<P>
The BJP-led government would consider the issue of insurance
reforms expeditiously and put in place a strong regulatory
mechanism for healthy participation by other players, he further
said. 
