<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin has
urged local governments to fully support the development of
township-run enterprises in China.
</P>
<P>
During a recent inspection tour in Jiangsu Province, east
China, Jiang said developing township enterprises is an important
strategy and a long-term, fundamental policy of China.
</P>
<P>
He said township enterprises have played an important role in
the modernation of agriculture and the industrialization of rural
areas.
</P>
<P>
A good performance of township enterprises is very important
for China to attain this year's goal for economic development,
stabilize and strengthen agriculture, and press ahead with the
reform of state-run enterprises as well, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that township enterprises should pay more
attention to technology upgrading and management improvement. They
should form enterprise groups to increase competitiveness and
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The president urged governments at all levels to attach great
importance to township enterprise development and give them
support in credit loans, using foreign capitals and technical
renovations.
</P>
<P>
During his inspection tour on April 20-22, the president
visited a number of township enterprises in Jiangsu province and
exchanged views with local officials, enterprise managers and
technicians on the development of those enterprises. 
