<HEADLINE> U.S. Proposes Pilot Training Program With Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The United States Defense
Department has proposed a 138-million-U.S.-dollar pilot training
program with the government of Singapore, the Singapore television
said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The proposed deal would help Singapore continue a long-term
pilot training program, the television report said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Defense Department was quoted as saying that it would
provide logistical support, aircraft modifications, support
equipment, fueling services and personnel services.
</P>
<P>
The program would help "to improve the security of a friendly
country which has been and continues to be an important force for
economic progress in Southeast Asia," it said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Singapore needed the services and equipment to
continue a long term pilot training program based at Luke Air
Force Base in Arizona, the Defense Department said. 
</P>
