<HEADLINE> Lakers' Harris Named NBA Coach of Month in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Del Harris of the Los Angeles
Lakers was named the NBA Coach of the Month in April, the NBA Asia
said in a press release on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Harris guided Los Angeles to an NBA-best 9-1 record during the
month, including 6-0 on the road as the Lakers (61-21) won at
least 50 games for the third consecutive season.
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles improved its win total for the fourth consecutive
campaign and moved to within two seasons of tying the NBA record
established by six teams for most consecutive seasons with an
improved winning percentage.
</P>
<P>
Harris, with 550 wins against 451 losses, coached in the
1,000th game of his career on April 17 against Dallas and now
ranked tied for 17th on the all-time coaching victories list.
</P>
<P>
For the month, Los Angeles ranked first in the NBA in
rebounding (47.4 rebounds per game), second in scoring (107.7
points per game), third in field goal percentage (50.2 percent)
and fourth in shot blocking (6.8 blocks per game).
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for the Coach of the Month were Atlanta's
Lenny Wilkens, Indiana's Larry Bird, Minnesota's Phil Saunders,
Phoenix's Danny Ainge and Utah's Jerry Sloan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
