<HEADLINE> Iran Opposes Laying Pipeline on Caspian Bed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi announced on Wednesday that Tehran is against laying a
pipeline on the bed of the Caspian Sea bed, terming it a violation
of the rights of other littoral countries.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the official Islamic Republic News Agency, Kharrazi
said that no party, especially no foreign company, can move in
violation of the rights of others' because there is no consensus
among the Caspian states over a new legal regime for the sea.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that Turkmenistan would possibly conclude a
contract with the United States for feasibility studies on laying
a pipeline on the Caspian bed linking it with Azerbaijan.
</P>
<P>
Kharrazi stated both Iran and Russia have already expressed
opposition to laying such a pipeline also due to environmental
considerations, adding that they would not allow others to make
one-sided decisions.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that the Caspian belongs to all littoral states -
Russia, Iran, Turkmenistan, Azerbaijan and Kazakhstan - which he
said should set up the legal framework for the largest lake in the
world.
</P>
<P>
Iran has repeatedly called for collective efforts to regulate
utilization of the Caspian's and exploitation of its natural
resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
