<DOCNO> XIE19980422.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clan Fighting Kills 3 in Southern Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 22 (Xinhua) -- At least three people were
killed and seven others wounded when heavy fighting broke out
between the Marehan and Majerten subclans in the village of
Gobwein, 18 km north of Somalia's southern port town of Kismaio
late Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to reports received through VHR radios, the attack
was launched by the Majerten subclan based inside Kismaio led by
General Mohamed Said Hirsi Morgan. The sources said one Marehan
subclansman was dead while four others suffered heavy gunshot
wounds.
</P>
<P>
The fighting in which nine technicals were used lasted for
more than an hour before the Majerten subclan was forced to
retreat back to their base. The village of Gobwein has been a
strong militia base for the Marehan subclan since they were
driven out of Kismaio last year.
</P>
<P>
The atmosphere has been tense with growing military build up
inside Kismaio since General Morgan arrived in the town about a
week ago, while the Marehan militia are gathering outside the
town.
</P>
<P>
The southern port town of Kismaio, 500 km south of the capital
Mogadishu, has been a focal point for armed clashes between the
two pastoral subclans over the control of the key positions of
Kismaio in the past two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
