<BODY>
<HEADLINE> O'Neal Named NBA Player of Month in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Center Shaquille O'Neal of the
Los Angeles Lakers was named NBA Player of the Month in April, a
press released from the NBA Asia said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
O'Neal helped lead the Lakers to an NBA-best 9-1 record by
averaging 33.8 points, 10.5 rebounds, 2.7 assists and 2.1 blocked
shots per game during the month.
</P>
<P>
He shot 131 for 212 from the field and ranked first in scoring,
second in field-goal percentage, eighth in rebounding and 10th in
shot blocking among league leaders in April.
</P>
<P>
"Shaquille continues to be a model of consistency in every
category -- scoring, rebounding and shot blocking to name a few,"
said L.A.Lakers head coach Del Harris. "His all-around game has
really improved in the last year or so, and that can only benefit
us down the road."
</P>
<P>
The Lakers led all teams except New Jersey (110.3 points per
game) in scoring during the month with 107.7 points per game,
thanks in large part to O'Neal's consistent offense.
</P>
<P>
He scored 20 or more points in all 10 games and had 30 or more
points seven times and 35 or more points four times. He led his
team in scoring and rebounding 10 and five times respectively.
</P>
<P>
O'Neal had several standout performances during the month
including 50 points and nine rebounds in a 117-106 win at New
Jersey on April 2 and 43 points (18 for 22 shooting), five
rebounds and four blocked shots in 33 minutes in a 124-95 defeat
of Dallas on April 17.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA Player of the Month were Chicago's
Michael Jordan, Minnesota's Kevin Garnett and Stephon Marbury, New
Jersey's Sam Cassell, Philadelphia's Allen Iverson, Phoenix's
Jason Kidd, San Antonio's Tim Duncan and Utah's Karl Malone.
</P>
</TEXT>
