<HEADLINE> China Now World's Largest Ceramics Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- China is producing 1.58 billion
sq.m. of ceramic tiles for buildings and 55 million units of
ceramic bathroom products, according to Liu Jingzhou, the
vice-chairman of the China Council for the Promotion of
International Trade's Building Materials Branch.
</P>
<P>
Liu said at the opening ceremony of the China International
Ceramics Exhibition yesterday that China has at least 800
companies making these materials and thousands of township-run
enterprises, and the cities of Foshan, Tangshan, and Boshan have
become its largest ceramics producers.
</P>
<P>
The country builds 300 million sq.m. of urban housing annually
and 600 million sq.m. in rural areas, and this has benefitted the
ceramics industry, he said, and, by the year 2000, China is
expected to add 230 new cities and 5,000 towns.
</P>
<P>
Greater Sino-foreign cooperation and technology exchanges have
helped the industry also, he said. More than 440 businesses have
introduced complete production lines from abroad, like automatic
machines from Italy, Germany, and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The five-day ceramics exhibition is sponsored by the Building
Materials Branch of the council and the China Ceramics
Association. It is China's largest ceramics exhibition, with
10,000 sq.m. of floor space. The major participants are from
Italy, Germany, the United States, Britain, Japan, Spain, Hong
Kong, and Taiwan, Liu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
