<DOCNO> XIE19980422.0156 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Inflation Rate Reaches 2.3 Percent in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Inflation rate between January and
March reached 2.3 percent in Macao, latest statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
on Wednesday also show that the composite consumer price index
(CCPI) grew 2.4 percent in March from the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
But the index for March was 0.1 percent down from February,
mainly because of price drops in such areas as telecommunications,
drug and medicine and some service sectors.
</P>
<P>
Macao's economic growth suffered a slowdown since 1993. The
growth for 1997 was estimated at less than one percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
