<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong-Spain Trade Grows in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The value of total trade
between Hong Kong and Spain in 1997 reached 1.9 billion U.S.
dollars, a six percent increase over a year earlier, the Spanish
Trade Commission in Hong Kong announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the total trade, 32 percent was due to exports to Hong Kong
from Spain of over 614 million U.S. dollars, representing a two
percent increase over the previous year. Around 50 percent of the
Spanish products were re-exported to the Chinese inland from Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
Ernesto Tejedor, trade commissioner of Spain in Hong Kong, said
at a press conference here that these results are especially
pleasing when considering that Hong Kong-Spain trade has grown at
a faster rate compared to Hong Kong's trade growth with the rest
of the world last year.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is Spain's second largest market in Asia.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, around 20 percent of Spanish exports to Hong Kong were
construction materials, followed by iron and steel and footwear.
</P>
<P>
Despite Asia's financial crisis, exports of Spanish shoes to
Hong Kong last year achieved a record 77 million U.S. dollars, a
59 percent jump year-on-year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Hong Kong is Spain's second largest supplier in Asia
after Japan. The value of Hong Kong's export to Spain amounted to
over 1.3 billion U.S. dollars last year, 90 percent of which were
of the Chinese inland origin including toys and radios.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's domestic exports to Spain are mainly clothing and
watches and clocks, reaching over 57 million U.S. dollars and 20
million U.S. dollars respectively in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Tejedor attributed the year-on-year increasing trade between
Hong Kong and Spain mainly to their good relationship and a free
trade policy that Hong Kong is implementing.
</P>
<P>
To further promote Spanish products and services in the Asia
Pacific market, he said the Spanish trade Commission and the
Spanish Institute for Foreign Trade have organized a Spanish
contingency at the upcoming Asia Pacific Leather Fair Spring Show
to be held in Hong Kong from April 30 to May 2.
</P>
<P>
"We are very confident that Spanish products and services will
continue to make substantial progress" in Hong Kong, the Chinese
inland and Asia as a whole, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
