<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Industrial Bank Issues First Batch of Housing Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai branch of China's
Industrial and Commercial Bank on Tuesday offered its first batch
of housing loans for this year worth 2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The loans, accounting for 10 percent of the total projected by
the bank for this year, come in a variety of forms. The largest
credit amount is 70 percent of the mortgage valued at 500,000 yuan
with a 20-year repayment term.
</P>
<P>
The bank has designated 60 outlets in the city to facilitate
the applicants. It has also provided services for buyers from Hong
Kong, Macao and Taiwan as well as those from overseas.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's housing loans are expected to increase at an annual
rate of 20 percent in the next decade, since the housing market is
entering a brisk period.
</P>
<P>
Insiders from Shanghai's commercial banks say that housing
credits are not only lucrative, since the overdue rate is as low
as four per 10,000, but also conducive to tapping the consumption
potential and promoting the sales of commercial housing.
</P>
<P>
Commercial banks here have issued more than 1 billion yuan of
loans for individual housing in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
