<HEADLINE> France to Keep Gold Reserve After Adopting Euro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 22 (Xinhua) -- France's central bank, the Bank of
France, will keep its gold reserve after replacing the franc with
the euro, said French Minister of Finance, Economy and Industry
Dominique Strauss-Kahn Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Europe 1 Television, Strauss-Kahn said
part of the gold reserve "will serve to defend the euro."
</P>
<P>
Other European countries will also offer their shares of gold
for defending the euro, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said the euro will be as strong as the French franc and
Deutsche mark as is shown through their exchange rates with the
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
"The euro will be a strong money in such a sense as allowing
France and other countries which join it to escape the logic (of
speculation) of the market," the French minister stressed. 
</P>
