<HEADLINE> Shanghai Airlines Opens Second Route to Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Airlines is now
offering a new route from Shanghai to Yinchuan, capital of
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
It is the second air route from Shanghai to northwest China
after the route from Shanghai to Xi'an, capital of northwest
China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The return Shanghai-Yinchuan flight will include a brief
stopover in Xi'an. The flight will depart Shanghai at 13:50 pm on
Wednesday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The company will operate Boeing 757 and 737 airliners for the
new route.
</P>
<P>
Yinchuan, which covers 1,457 sq.km., is home to over one
million people, with members of the Hui minority nationality
accounting for some 18 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The new route will greatly enhance economic ties, tourism and
cultural exchanges between Shanghai and the economically backward
midwestern region. 
</P>
