<HEADLINE> China's Largest Tyre Producer Going into Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Tire Rubber Group
Co. (STRG), the largest tire manufacturer in China, signed a
merger agreement with the Luoyang Tire Plant on Tuesday to form
China's biggest tire production center for agricultural machinery.
</P>
<P>
The merger will adjust the product mix in an ever-changing tire
market and allow the manufacture of high-tech products at a
comparatively low cost, according to insiders.
</P>
<P>
The new company will be based in the Luoyang High-Tech and
New-Technology Zone in Luoyang, central China's Henan Province. An
annual output of 1.5 million tires and an annual turnover of 650
million yuan have been designed.
</P>
<P>
The former Luoyang Tire Plant was a state-owned enterprise
capable of producing 96 varieties of tires. It had 330 million
yuan in output value and 17.03 million yuan in pre-tax profit last
year. No losses or lay-offs were recorded before the merger.
</P>
<P>
STRG ranked 14th among the world's 50 top tire producers in
1996, with last year's turnover reaching 5.3 billion yuan and a
net profit exceeding 200 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
