<HEADLINE> China Urges Workers to Emulate New Generation Model Worker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Today's editions of People's
Daily, Workers Daily, China Youth Daily and various other
Beijing-based newspapers frontpaged articles on Wang Tao, a modern
Chinese model worker in an automobile plant.
</P>
<P>
Wang Tao is different from iron worker Wang Jinxi, a model
worker in northeast China's Daqing Oilfield in the 1960s, in that
he not only works hard, but has also authored four books on motor
vehicle structures and adjustment procedures.
</P>
<P>
Hard and assiduous work was most important criterion for model
workers in the 1960s and 1970s.
</P>
<P>
Wang works for the Dongfeng Automobile Company in Shiyan City,
central China's Hubei Province, and is in charge of assembling and
checking motor vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The modern model worker, who has worked for the company for 23
consecutive years, has an unblemished record and invented the
"Wang Tao Operations Technique" which has greatly improved work
efficiency.
</P>
<P>
"Engineer Wang", a reference used by fellow workers, has
consulted with experts concerning technological problems and has
purchases numerous books related to his work.
</P>
<P>
He has been won both national and provincial model worker
titles for 12 years in a row.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
