<HEADLINE> Hu Jintao Meets Japanese Parliamentary Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao Wednesday spoke highly of the role that the Chinese and
Japanese parliaments have played in enhancing Sino-Japanese
relations.
</P>
<P>
Meeting separately with Japan's House of Representatives
speaker Soichiro Ito and House of Councillors president Juro
Saito, Hu said parliament diplomacy constitutes an important part
of state-to-state relations.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) and Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) value their
friendly ties with Japanese Diet (parliament), said Hu.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Japanese Diet has accumulated rich experience
in legislature and hoped that the parliaments of China and Japan
would boost bilateral cooperation to play an even bigger role in
fostering Sino-Japanese friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that Sino-Japanese cooperation in various fields has
witnessed remarkable progress since the normalization of bilateral
ties thanks to the efforts of the two countries' governments,
parliaments, political parties and people from all walks of life.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Communist Party and government will as always carry
out the good-neighborly and cooperative policy toward Japan, Hu
added.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president briefed the Japanese Legislators on the
formation and function of the NPC and China's political system.
</P>
<P>
Ito said that Hu's current Japan tour and the upcoming visit to
Japan by Chinese President Jiang Zemin would greatly advance
friendly relations between China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
He said that the principles set in Japan-China Joint Statement
and Japan-China Peace and Friendship Treaty are the foundation of
bilateral ties. The Japanese Diet would firmly abide by these
principles and work for a friendly Japan-China relationship
oriented toward the next century, he added.
</P>
<P>
Saito said the fact that Hu chose Japan as the first country of
his overseas trip after assuming vice presidency demonstrated that
China treasures its ties with Japan.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese Diet is willing to expand exchange with China's
NPC, he told Hu.
</P>
<P>
He said that Japan would not allow the unfortunate history to
repeat and would promote Japan-China friendly relations on the
basis of serious introspection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
