<DOCNO> XIE19980422.0214 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: Measures Taken To Ensure Economic Growth (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhang Hanya, director of the Investment Research Institute
under the State Development Planning Commission, said the present
financial and material resources of China make it possible for the
country to raise the growth rate of investment to 20 percent in
the 1998-99 period.
</P>
<P>
To create greater domestic demand, the government will abolish
the century-old practice of welfare distribution of residential
houses in the latter half of the year, expand the scale of
mortgage loans and develop a real estate secondary market.
</P>
<P>
Though the buyer's market hampers China's economic development
for the time being, many government officials and economists are
confident in economic growth by raising investment.
</P>
<P>
In the last couple of years, market demand for residential
houses, cars and computers has been spiraling. Massive
construction of infrastructure projects has also driven the
development of related industries.
</P>
<P>
Several years ago, some Chinese experts predicted that a new
economic development period would start in 1997. Facts proved that
the real start of the new period will be made this year.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, people have every reason to believe that a sustained
high economic growth rate is far from termination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
