<HEADLINE> Chinese Baby Carriages Welcomed in US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- "Cosco Geoby", Chinese brand name
strollers, are selling well in the United States, according to
today's edition of Economic Daily.
</P>
<P>
The strollers, manufactured by the Good Baby Group in Kunshan,
east China's Jiangsu Province, entered the U.S. market at the end
of 1996, and gained a third place ranking in the baby carriage
market during 1997.
</P>
<P>
Geoby, a moniker meaning "good boy", attracted over 600,000
orders during the Dallas Children's Products Trade Fair held in
February this year.
</P>
<P>
Group General Manager Song Zhenghuan said the secret of Geoby's
success lies in the company's timely and in-depth studies
of trends on the U.S. market. The company has also established an
information system in the United States to ensure timely feedback.
</P>
<P>
Good Baby twin-seat stroller model immediately attracted the
attention of young parents in the United States. The model was
first displayed in February, 1997, with over 50,000 orders for the
product received during March.
</P>
<P>
The company also attributed its success to Cosco, its
U.S. agent which enjoys an impeccable reputation and strong sales
network.  
</P>
