<DOCNO> XIE19980422.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Salaries for Web-related Jobs Surveyed in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Salaries for Internet and
Web-related jobs in the United States range roughly from 40,000 to
120,000 U.S. dollars a year, according to the findings of a survey
released Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The survey, the first of its kind conducted by the American
Electronics Association, was carried out on 19 large companies,
including Netscape Communications, Yahoo Inc., CNET and Cisco
System.
</P>
<P>
It covers more than 30 of the "hottest" Internet positions
within engineering, design, administration, marketing/sales and
Web content groups.
</P>
<P>
As with many sectors of high technology, all of the jobs
surveyed substantially outpaced the private sector wage average of
28,582 dollars, the association said.
</P>
<P>
Start-ups can be 10 to 20 percent lower than the big companies
when it comes to base salary. Sometimes they are even 10,000 to
20,000 dollars lower, and offering stock or other kinds of
alternative compensation are usual ways to make up for the loss.
</P>
<P>
The highest salaries, with an average of 121,200 dollars a
year, are paid to "Internet strategists," who develop strategy for
use of the Internet in support of division or company goals. This
job requires a bachelor's degree in computer science, business or
marketing and three to five years' experience in information
systems design.
</P>
<P>
Next come electronics commerce managers, who manage Internet
commerce for a business unit. The job requires a bachelor's degree
in computer science or business, plus several years of experience
in defining business systems. They earn 120,100 dollars a year.
</P>
<P>
Those who earn 78,500 dollars and 76,700 dollars are Web
publishers and Internet engineers. The former directs staff that
produces content for Web projects, and the latter acts as
technical resource for company's Internet unit.
</P>
<P>
Forum managers, Web editors and graphic artists earn between
50,000 and 45,000 dollars. Forum manager handles an Internet chat
room and needs basic knowledge of online tools and company
policies.
</P>
<P>
A Web editor develops content for web sites and is required to
have a bachelor's degree in English, journalism experience,
knowledge of hypetext markup language (HTML) and Web-page
design. Graphic artists use online tools to solve routine
technical design problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
