<HEADLINE> Four Prairie Fires Put out in Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Forestry wardens and local
firefighters extinguished three wildfires this morning in north
China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
One of the major fires, which spread from a Chen Barag Banner
(county) coal mine in Hulun Buir League (prefecture) beginning on
the afternoon of April 19, killed one local resident and injured
six, with one person reported as missing, according to officials.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which spread quickly due to prevailing strong
winds, destroyed some 20-odd Mongolian yurts belonging to nomadic
families, in addition to either killing or seriously burning some
1,500 head of livestock, including cows and sheep.
</P>
<P>
Forestry wardens and firefighters successfully extinguished
the fire this morning, as well as two prairie fires in Hinggan
League which borders on Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Local sources also note that another major fire, which spread
from Mongolia to Xin Barag Banner in Hulun Buir League, was
extinguished on April 20.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government organized thousands of police officers
and firefighters to the battle four fires. No casualties were
reported for the large force battling the fires. 
</P>
</TEXT>
