<HEADLINE> Portuguese Prime Minister Visits Products, Technology Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Portugal's Prime Minister Antonio
Guterres attended the opening ceremony here today of an exhibition
of products and technology from Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Guterres said that bilateral political ties have been
developing smoothly since his country and China forged diplomatic
relations 19 years ago, and that there is broad potential for
future economic cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
China has achieved in great successes in reform and opening-up,
while Portugal's economy is developing toward
internationalization, Guterres said, adding that he hoped the two
sides would seize such a sound opportunity and push bilateral
economic and trade cooperation to a new high.
</P>
<P>
Guterres said both governments support the cooperation between
entrepreneurs of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is part of Portugal's strategy to develop
economic and trade ties with China, Guterres said, adding that the
fourth meeting of the Sino-Portugal Economic and Trade Committee
which will be held this fall will further improve such cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said his country is willing to contribute to
economic ties between the European Union and China.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xinhua, vice-minister of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, said at the opening ceremony that China's sustained
and rapid economic development and huge market provide opportunities
for Portuguese enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Chen said he hopes the two sides will set out from a strategic
height, have their eyes on the 21st century and seize the
opportunity to improve bilateral ties and economic and trade
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese State Councillor Wu Yi, Portugal's Foreign Minister
Jaime Gama and Portugal's Economic Minister Joaquim Pina Moura
also attended the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is the first of its kind Portugal has ever
held in China. More than 60 enterprises from Portugal are
participating in the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Guterres also attended a China-Portugal workshop on
biotechnology here today. He said that the advancement of science
and technology should not be dominated by several developed
countries, and that China has made achievements in the field even
though it is a developing country.
</P>
<P>
China is Portugal's ideal cooperative partner in science and
technology, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
