<HEADLINE> Beijing Airport Introduces U.S. Bird-Relocation Devices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Capital International
Airport has begun to use more than 120 bird-relocation devices to
improve flight safety.
</P>
<P>
The solar-energy and computer auto-inductive devices from the
United States have been installed 60 meters away from the east and
west runways of the country's biggest airport.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the administrative department of the airport said
the devices have proved to be quite effective in driving birds out
of the airport in the past 20 days of operation.
</P>
<P>
With the improvement of the environment in the airport area, an
increasing number of birds has threatened the safety of aircraft
landing and taking off from the airport.
</P>
<P>
In October, the airport was forced to close for two hours in
the afternoons for several days as many swallows gathered at the
airport's runways.
</P>
<P>
Before the installation of the devices, the airport had used
many methods to relocate the birds, such as asking workers to
drive out birds and firing warning shoots. However, the methods
were ineffective.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
