<HEADLINE> East China Development Zone Reports Robust Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Suzhou State New and
High-Technology Development Zone in east China's Jiangsu Province
reported robust growth in the first quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that the zone, which was founded six
years ago, turned out an industrial output value of more than 3.35
billion yuan in the first three months, a rise of 34.9 percent
over the same period last year. The zone's quarterly profit surged
73.3 percent year-on-year to 117 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Contracted overseas investment for projects approved in the
zone in the first quarter totaled 117 million U.S. dollars, the
largest among similar zones in Jiangsu, one of China's economic
powerhouses.
</P>
<P>
During the past six years, the zone has invested 3 billion yuan
in infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
As the overall investment environment improves, more overseas
companies are making their way into the zone. Overseas companies,
including 50 multinational corporations, had funded more than 300
projects in the zone by early this month, with total investment
hitting 3.6 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The Asian financial crisis has not affected the zone
considerably, though investors from Japan, Hong Kong and Taiwan
regions account for a large proportion of all overseas investment
in the zone, according to one official.
</P>
<P>
The overall economic efficiency of firms in the zone doubled in
the first quarter, the official added.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Japanese Jiangsu Fuji Communications Technology
Co. Ltd., for example, reported a profit of 29.54 million yuan in
the first quarter, a surge of 157 percent over a year ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
