<HEADLINE> Southwest China To Seek Foreign Funds for State Firms' Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province has announced that it will try to attract more foreign
funds this year into part of its money-losing state enterprises
through mergers and joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
The province will also work to get foreign investment in
infrastructure construction, agricultural resources development,
high-tech industry and tourism.
