<HEADLINE> Inland, Hong Kong Venture To Cooperate in Oil Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 22 (Xinhua) -- An inland oil company and a Hong
Kong petroleum company plan to start prospecting in the Lengjia
Oil Field in northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
It will be the biggest cooperative oil development project in
China's inland areas.
</P>
<P>
China Petroleum Corp. of Hong Kong holds 70 percent of the
development rights with more than one billion yuan (120 million
U.S. dollars) of investment and the Lengjia Oil Field holds 30
percent.
</P>
<P>
The cooperative project will be launched in a
278-square-kilometer block. The oil field is considered rich in
thick oil. Lengjia is part of the Liaohe Oil Field, China's third
largest oil field.
</P>
<P>
Lengjia Oil Field produces 1.25 million tons of oil last year.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong company has already invested in the Karamay Oil
Field in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region.  
</P>
