<HEADLINE> Paraguay to Hold Presidential Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The Paraguayan Superior
Court of Electoral Justice said the country's presidential
elections will be held on May 10 as scheduled, said reports from
Asuncion, the capital of Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Mojoli, president of the electoral court, discarded
reports on Tuesday of any election postponement. He said there is
no authority with power enough to change the constitutional terms.
</P>
<P>
After presenting a new candidate list, the ruling Partido
Colorado party asked for a postponement. They argued that their
new candidates would not have enough time to prepare themselves
for the May 10 election as well as other candidates, and thus a
temporary postponement of the election would be fair.
</P>
<P>
The request was denied by the major opposition, the
Democratic Alliance, which is formed by the Authentic
Liberal Radical and the Encuentro Nacional parties.
</P>
<P>
The Partido Colorado party changed its candidacy list because
its presidential candidate, former General Lino Oviedo, is now
politically incapacitated. He was sentenced to 10 years in jail
for plotting a coup d'etat.
</P>
<P>
On the new list, Oviedo was replaced by his colleague, Raul
Cubas Grau, who transferred his former vice-presidential candidacy
to another leader of the party, Luis Maria Argana. 
</P>
</TEXT>
