<HEADLINE> Tianjin Uses Foreign Funds to Exploit Geothermal Heat Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 22 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin is making better use of
its rich geothermal heat resources with the help of advanced
technology from Iceland.
</P>
<P>
With the assistance of experts from Iceland, the city has
successfully dug three high-quality 2,000-meter-deep geothermal
wells in the Tanggu beach area and installed computerized heat and
water supply systems. The project, which took more than two years
to complete, cost 30,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
By employing Iceland's technology and computer software,
mathematical models on underground heat reserves at Tanggu have
been established.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Tanggu Underground Heat Experiment and Research
Center is expected to be set up soon to help with the city's plan
to make further use of geothermal heat to make mineral water
drinks, build swimming pools, bathrooms, and breeding
farms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
