<HEADLINE> Poll: Hi-Tech Shares To Lead Stock Markets in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- "Who will lead the stock markets
in China? Hi-tech shares," says a recent survey in Shanghai, the
country's largest economic and financial powerhouse and home to
one of the only two exchanges in the country.
</P>
<P>
The poll was conducted by the Shanghai Securities News among
200 local investors. Shanghai has more than 2.5 milliion stock
investors.
</P>
<P>
Of the people surveyed, 53 percent pin high hopes on hi-tech
shares, while nearly one-third favor the Hongqiao Airport.
</P>
<P>
Hi-tech shares, with a volume of 50 million to 80 million
shares each and moderate prices of 10 to 20 yuan are most likely
to lead the markets, they believe.
</P>
<P>
The poll indicates an optimistic market for local investors
this year because of favorable state policies on stock trading,
government policy to reinvigorate the nation through developing
science and education, and bullish international stock markets.
