<HEADLINE> Central China's Luoyang Attracts More Outside Investments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The city of Luoyang has become
central China's new magnet for investment, signified by
construction of the Xiaolangdi water conservation project on the
Yellow River with an investment of 40 billion yuan and a large
chemical fiber project with an investment of 4.95 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
An official from the provincial government said that, as the
largest industrial city in central China's Henan Province, Luoyang
will extend several major projects with investments of 65 billion
yuan during the 1996-2000 period including transforming the old
industrial center and expanding thermo-electricity stations.
</P>
<P>
Xiaolangdi scenic zone has attracted 70 investors from overseas
as well as domestic investment. About 21 projects are under
construction or in operation, with investment expected to reach
380 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The state's major project -- the Luoyang chemical fiber project
-- started operation in February of 1998, and is expected to
produce 200,000 tons of polyester annually. In accordance with the
project, a petrochemical city will be set up in the northern part
of Luoyang.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, the petrochemical industry output value of Luoyang is
expected to reach 10 billion yuan, with total profits exceeding 3
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Progress has also been reported in transforming the old
industrial base with an investment exceeding 4.9 billion yuan; 11
projects have become part of the state's plan.
</P>
<P>
During the 1996-2000 period, Luoyang is expected to add 1.98
million kilowatts of installed capacity. Up to now, Luoyang formed
six pillar industries including machine-building, eletronics,
metallurgy, building materials, petrochemicals, light industry and
food processing.
</P>
<P>
Luoyang has attracted investors from more than 20 countries and
regions. By 1997, the city had approved more than 483
foreign-funded enterprises with a total investment of 1.84 billion
U.S. dollars. The city also completed exports of 204 million U.S.
dollars, ranking first in Henan Province.  
</P>
</TEXT>
