<HEADLINE> Michael Chang Wins Opener in US Clay Court Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Top seed and defending
champion Michael Chang of the United States defeated Paraguay's
Ramon Delgado before winning his opener in three sets at the ATP
US Clay Court Championships in Orlando, Florida on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chang, who has fallen from second to 12th in world rankings,
overwhelmed Delgado 6-4, 3-6, 7-6 (7-1) at the 315,000
U.S. dollars event.
</P>
<P>
Chang has struggled with a recent knee injury. Since winning in
Orlando a year ago he has been ousted 11 times in early rounds and
taken only one title.
</P>
