<HEADLINE> Larsen Seeks Fourth Win in Euro Badminton Singles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen of Denmark
began his quest for another place in history with two convincing
victories at the European Badminton Championships on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
32-year-old Hoyer-Larsen is bidding to become the first player
to win the men's singles four championships in a row. He currently
shares the record with fellow-Dane Flemming Delfs.
</P>
<P>
Second seeded Hoyer-Larsen is relieved that he is in the
opposite half of the draw from his Danish team mates, top seed
Peter Gade Christensen, who is the world number two, and world
champion, Peter Rasmussen.
</P>
<P>
Hoyer-Larsen had little difficulty in beating his first two
opponents to reach the last 16.
</P>
<P>
He defeated Evgenji Isakov of Russia 15-4, 15-6 and then edged
England's Robert Nock 15-11, 15-8.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, top seed and defending champion Camilla
Martin of Denmark, easily entered the last 16. In the first round
she downed Filipa Lamy of Portugal 11-1, 11-3 and in the second
she spent about ten minutes to win over Marketa Koudelokova 11-2,
11-0. 
</P>
