<HEADLINE> More Heroin Refinery Camps Busted in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 22 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized
nine more heroin refinery camps in some anti-drug operations in
the past two months in the northern part of the country, the
official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the nine camps raided by columns of the Myanmar Armed
Forces, four were destroyed in Muse township's Heymonelon and
Namsu areas on March 23 while the rest were captured in Kutkai
township on April 6.
</P>
<P>
A great deal of narcotic drugs including heroin, opium and
other chemicals used in refining heroin were confiscated in the
two operations, the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the authorities seized three
heroin refineries in Shan State earlier this year and 33 others in
1997. 
</P>
