<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Electronic Giants in China Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 22 (Xinhua) -- China announced this month a list
of its top 100 electronic companies in 1998, with Changhong,
China's largest TV maker from Sichuan Province, leading the field
for the third consecutive year, according to today's "China Daily."
</P>
<P>
The first three largest companies in terms of sales are Sichuan
Changhong Electronic Group Co, Legend Group Company, and Shanghai
Video &AMP; Audio Elect (Group) Co Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The first three most-profitable electronics enterprises in 1998
are Sichuan Changhong Electronics Group Co, Shanghai Bell
Telephone Equipment Manufacturing Co Ltd, and Shanghai Video &AMP;
Audio Elect (Group) Co Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The overall strength of China's electronic enterprises grew
substantially last year. The sum of the sales of the top 100
electronics enterprises grew 34.5 percent to 200.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Sales of the top 100 enterprises accounted for 76 percent of
the overall figure of China's electronics industry, up four
percentage points over 1997.
</P>
<P>
Most of these enterprises manufacture TVs, computers,
computerized switching machines, VCD players, telephones, mobile
phones and colour picture tubes.
</P>
<P>
The total profits of the top 100 enterprises was 14.46 billion
yuan (1.74 billion US dollars), up 35.1 percent from
1997. Enterprises with annual profits over 100 million yuan (12.05
million US dollars) totalled 30, compared with 26 last year.
</P>
<P>
The list also revealed that telecommunications and computer
enterprises are gaining prominence amongst the overall top 100
electronic companies.
</P>
<P>
Beginning in 1987, the list of the country's top 100
electronics enterprises experienced the greatest changes, with 18
players dropping out of the list.  
</P>
</TEXT>
