<HEADLINE> Derailed Trolley Kills One, Injures Others in Vienna </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- A derailed trolley in Vienna
crashed into a bank on Tuesday and killed a 19-year-old female
clerk and injured several passengers.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place at a rail crossing on Simmering
Street. A route number 71 trolley derailed for overspeeding.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the derailing, the second car of the two-car
trolley rammed into the bank, which was situated on a corner,
after it slammed against the first car.
</P>
<P>
A number of the 48 passengers on board the two cars were
seriously injured, while others escaped with only minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
According competent authorities, the driver may possibly be
held responsible for the accident. The accident however is still
under investigation.
</P>
<P>
When the accident occurred, the trolley was traveling at a
speed of 47 kilometers per hour, far in excess of the 15 kilometer
per hour speed limit in the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
