<HEADLINE> Mao Zedong's Home Village Starts Clean-up Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A campaign is under way in Mao
Zedong's home village of Shaoshan to eliminate unethical business
practices and to provide a better environment for visitors.
</P>
<P>
The campaign centers on Mao's former residence, memorial hall,
bronze statue square and other attractions. Local officials aim to
demolish unauthorized souvenir shops and commercial buildings, ban
superstitious activities, clear away unhealthy publications and
souvenirs and rectify the parking situation.
</P>
<P>
Shaoshan in central China's Hunan Province attracts millions of
visitors a year. In the midst of a tourism boom, problems such as
illegal construction of commercial venues, disorder in the
management around scenic areas, and rampant superstitious
activities have been plaguing the village. 
</P>
