<HEADLINE> Cuba, Dominican Republic Resume Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Cuba announced Tuesday that it
will reestablish full diplomatic relations with the Dominican
Republic interrupted 38 years ago.
</P>
<P>
With the resumption of diplomatic ties with the Dominican
Republic, Havana has completed the process of reestablishing
relations with all the Caribbean countries, Cuban authorities said.
</P>
<P>
A joint declaration issued here said that the governments of
Cuba and the Dominican Republic were interested in further
improving neighborhood, friendship and cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
It said that the resumption of diplomatic relations contributes
to regional and hemispherical unity, particularly in Central
America and the Caribbean, where some integration process of
utmost importance is taking place.
</P>
<P>
Cuba and the Dominican Republic, which severed diplomatic
relations in 1960, renewed their links at the consular level last
June. Cuba now maintains diplomatic relations with 164 countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
