<HEADLINE> Brazilian President Visits Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZILIA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso left Tuesday for a five-day official visit to
Spain aimed at strengthening economic and trade relations.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Cardoso will meet Spanish leaders, including
King Juan Carlos I and Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar, and invite
Spanish businessmen to invest in Brazil, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
Apart from Madrid, Cardoso will also visit other Spanish cities
such as Salamanca and Santiago de Compostela.
</P>
<P>
With a total investment of more than 3.2 billion U.S. dollars,
Spain ranks as the second largest foreign investor in Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish investments have been mainly channeled to
sectors of energy, finance and communications.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral trade witnessed a 20 percent increase last year,
amounting to 2.1 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
King Juan Carlos I and Queen Dona Sofia are scheduled to visit
Brazil in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
