<BODY>
<HEADLINE> AEK Athens Advances to European Basketball Final . </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, April 21 (Xinhua) -- AEK Athens of Greece defeated
Benetton Treviso of Italy 69-66 to enter the final at the European
Championship basketball tournament in Barcelona on Tuesday but the
win was marred by serious crowd trouble.
</P>
<P>
Police battled with AEK fans for several minutes as violence
erupted for the third time in the evening.
</P>
<P>
There had been minor skirmishes before and during Italy's
Kinder Bologna's 83-61 victory over Partizan Belgrade of
Yugoslavia earlier in the evening.
</P>
<P>
But matters turned ugly within minutes of the end of the second
match and not for the first time Greek fans were at the center of
it.
</P>
<P>
Police moved in with batons to try to disperse the supporters.
There were no immediate reports of injuries or arrests.
</P>
<P>
On the court, American Willie Anderson led the Greek club to
victory with 21 points, several of them important ones at the end
of a see-saw game which Benetton, who had been level at 63-63,
conceded only in the final seconds. The match halftime score was
37-36 in favour of the winner.
</P>
<P>
Benetton's American Henry Williams scored 22 points for the
team's top scorer.
</P>
<P>
AEK will be bidding to become the third Greek side in
succession to win the championship following Olympiakos in 1997
and Panathinaikos the previous year.
</P>
<P>
In another semi-final match Earlier, Kinder Bologna edged
Partizan Belgrade 83-61 after leading 45-25 at halftime.
</P>
<P>
Zoran Savic led the way for the Italian side, top-scoring with
23 points. He was at the heart of an efficient Italian
performance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
