<HEADLINE> Albania, Holland Sign Agreement on Military Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Dutch Defense Minister
Joris Voorhoeve and his Albanian counterpart Sabit Brokaj on
Tuesday signed an agreement to increase military cooperation in
1998.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Albania will send staff officers to the
Netherlands for training and the two nations will conduct joint
military activities.
</P>
<P>
During the talks prior to the signing of the agreement, the two
defense ministers affirmed the relationship and cooperation
between the two countries and their military services.
</P>
<P>
Hoorhoeve said both being small countries, the Netherlands and
Albania should engage in mutual assistance and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries had great potential for enhancing
cooperation through a peaceful partnership. He hoped the
cooperation between the two military services would last.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian Defense Minister commended Holland for its support
of his country. Albania, he said, deemed its relationship with
Holland particularly valuable.
</P>
<P>
The two ministries of defense are expected to sign a memorandum
of understanding in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch defense delegation arrived here on Tuesday for a
two-day visit. 
</P>
