<HEADLINE> Mediterranean Forum Urges Closer Ties Among Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PALMA DE MAJORCA, Spain, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers
from 11 countries around the Mediterranean urged strengthened
political dialogue and cooperation in the region at the conclusion
of a two-day meeting here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ministers, attending an annual meeting of the Mediterranean
Forum, called for increased bilateral and multilateral cooperation
in fighting terrorism and organized crime.
</P>
<P>
They also urged more economic and cultural cooperation within
the Forum.
</P>
<P>
The representatives from Spain, France, Greece, Italy,
Portugal, Malta, Algeria, Egypt, Morocco, Tunisia and Turkey
expressed concerns over the deadlocked Middle East peace process,
demanding a strict implementation of related U.N. resolutions by
all sides.
</P>
<P>
The Forum, established in 1994, is an informal group for
exchanging opinions and debating issues among countries around the
Mediterranean. 
