<HEADLINE> Chinese Firm to Provide Pudong Airport With Power Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 22 (Xinhua) -- A company from suburban Fengxian
County of Shanghai has won the contract to supply medium-voltage
power distribution equipment to the first phase of the
international airport of Pudong New Area.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Key-Road General Electric Co. Ltd., a subsidiary of
the Zhezhong Group, won the contract after it beat 24 overseas
companies in an open international bidding.
</P>
<P>
Zhezhong Group, a rural enterprise, now has assets of 200
million yuan. It is considered a leader in power distribution
equipment in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The group, which has kept long-term technical cooperation ties
with foreign companies such as Westinghouse of the United States,
has passed the ISO9001 test of international quality standards and
holds quality certificates recognized by China, the United States
and Britain.
</P>
<P>
The international airport in Pudong New Area is now under
construction. In building the airport, Shanghai Pudong
International Airport Company, the developer, has introduced
international bidding to find cooperative partners on a fair and
effective basis.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the airport is expected to be finished and
put into service by Oct. 1, 1999, or the 50th anniversary of the
founding of People's Republic of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
