<HEADLINE> Drugs Seizures Rise at Vienna Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Vienna airport police seized 60
kilograms of cocaine in the first quarter of this year, four times
the amount siezed in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Alfred Rupf, chief of the anti-drugs team at the airport, told
reporters Tuesday that the amount of drugs seized in the first
quarter equals to that of the whole of 1997.
</P>
<P>
Austria has tightened grip on drug smuggling after the country
loosened tourism restrictions and opened its borders to Schengen
Accord member countries at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Vienna joined the accord in December 1997, allowing citizens of
member states can move freely within the accord area.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen European nations, including most European Union
members, have joined the accord, which was first signed in 1985
and came into effect 10 years later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
