<HEADLINE> German Economics Minister to Visit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 21 (Xinhua) -- Accompanied by a large business
delegation, German Economics Minister Guenter Rexrodt will leave
for a one-week visit to China this Friday in a bid to promote
German business activities in the country.
</P>
<P>
With its infrastructure and industries due to be modernized,
China offered vast opportunities for German business, especially
for machinery and capital goods manufacturers, Rexrodt said
Tuesday in Bonn.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, Rexrodt is due to participate in the seventh
Asian-Pacific Conference of German Economy on April 28-29 which is
expected to discuss the Asian financial crisis and explore future
cooperation possibilities between Germany and Asia.
</P>
<P>
The expected presence of a record number of about 700 business
leaders in the conference showed that despite the financial
turmoils the economic attractiveness of Asia was still unbroken
and that German companies still had confidence in the economic
outlook of the region, the German minister said.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Rexrodt will also open a German consumer
goods fair in Shanghai, the first-ever complete show of German
consumer goods industry in a foreign country. The tour will also
take Rexrodt to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Business leaders in the German delegation include president of
the Federal Federation of German Industry, Hans-Olaf Henkel,
president of the German Council of Commerce and Industry, Hans
Peter Stihl as well as chairman of the Asian-Pacific Committee of
German Economy and Siemens chief, Heinrich von Pierer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
