<HEADLINE> Dow Sets New High, Led by IBM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Stocks in New York rose to new
highs Tuesday, led by IBM which reported a 13 percent decline in
earnings.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 43.10 points to 9,184.94
in heavy trading, topping the previous high of 9,167.50 reached
Friday.
</P>
<P>
International Business Machines rose more than 6 percent and
led the Dow's gains. Even though it reported a 13 percent decline
in earnings late Monday as a result of fierce price wars, IBM
topped the diminished expectations of Wall Street analysts.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq composite index had its first close
above 1,900, and the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock index also
reached a new high.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by an 8-to-7 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with NYSE volume totaling 674.06
million shares, up sharply from 595.19 million on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The S&AMP;P 500 rose 2.69 to 1,126.34, and the NYSE composite index
rose 0.79 to a record 584.80.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 16.73 to 1,903.87, its first
foray above 1,900.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 2.60 to
491.41, and the small-company dominated American Stock Exchange
composite index rose 1.84 to 749.79, padding Monday's records for
both measures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
