<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Falls Broadly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 21 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar fell against
other major currencies Tuesday, sinking to an 11-week low against
the mark as the German and Swiss currencies gained strength.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 1.7884
marks, down from 1.8012 late Monday.
</P>
<P>
It also was changing hands at 131.35 yen, down from 132.15.
</P>
<P>
Economic reports from Germany led investors to feel that
Germany's economy was improving.
</P>
<P>
Overall, investors have begun worrying less about high European
unemployment and other problems. Economists predict some European
countries will raise interest rates as part of preparing for the
their single currency.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late Monday:
1.4805 Swiss francs, down from 1.4975; 5.9935 French francs, down
from 6.0390; 1,768.00 Italian lire, down from 1,781.30; and 1.4307
Canadian dollars, up from 1.4271.
</P>
<P>
The British pound was quoted at 1.6756 dollars, up from 1.6716
dollars. 
</P>
